    "rationale": "This is a classic and simple example of the Hofmann-Löffler-Freytag reaction. N-chloro-N-methylbutan-1-amine undergoes intramolecular 1,5-hydrogen atom transfer upon photolysis or acid catalysis, forming a delta-carbon radical. This radical then abstracts a chlorine atom to form a delta-chloroamine, which cyclizes upon treatment with base (generated in situ or added) to yield N-methylpyrrolidine. This example clearly demonstrates the key C-H activation at a remote (delta) position and subsequent cyclization to a five-membered ring, which is characteristic of the reaction.",
    "collision_avoidance_note": "This example uses a simple acyclic N-haloamine substrate and avoids complex structures, arenes, or other functional groups that could trigger unrelated named reaction queries. The core transformation is a remote C-H functionalization followed by cyclization, which is specific to this reaction family and distinct from other cyclization or rearrangement reactions like the Beckmann or Hofmann rearrangements."
  }
